        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<figure type="diagram"> 
<p>Statement of Sales of Origin of Species<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>for account of Cha<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> Darwin</p>
<p>On hand last account, 645 On hand this date, 522</p>
<p>Printed since, … 1000</p>
<p>Given away,</p>
<p>Sold to date, … 1123</p>
<p>1645 1645</p>
<p>Sold 1123 Copies @ 2$ Rate 5%  $112.30</p>
<p>Descent of Man</p>
<p>On hand last account, 2335 On hand this date, 1662</p>
<p>Printed since 2000 Given away, …</p>
<p>Sold to date, … 2673</p>
<p>4335 4335</p>
<p>Sold 2673 Copies @2$  Rate 10%  $534 60</p>
<p>* 646 90</p>
<p>Value in Stg Exch 110 Gold 114<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>£ 116.1.5</p> </figure> 
<p><lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin| Aug. 1/72</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">End of document:</hi> ‘Last a/c rendered Febry’<ref target="#foot.f3"/> <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">This statement gives sales figures for the US editions of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> and <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi> <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_135.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">D. Appleton &amp; Co</ref>. had issued a new edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> in 1870 based on the fifth English edition; another edition was printed in 1873, based on the sixth London edition (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Freeman 1977</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The value is given in sterling and gold.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from D. Appleton &amp; Co., 23 February 1872</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
